<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>Chris Kolb was a Democratic State Representative for the 53rd district (Ann Arbor and Pittsfield Township) from January 2001 to January 2007. He was especially involved in legislative issues relating to gay rights, land use and the environment, and health insurance.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>Kolb's papers include legislative files mainly relating to gay issues, including gay marriage and hate crime legislation. The Kolb papers have been divided into two series: Career Files and Legislative Files. </p>
</scopecontent>

